Callanan Scores in Tough Loss to Gaels at Torero Stadium
San Diego women's soccer put up a strong fight despite a 2-1 loss to Saint Mary's at Torero Stadium. The team, now 4-4-6 overall and 4-1-2 in the WCC, scored late in the match thanks to Ella Callanan. Junior goalkeeper Ilise Medrano made six saves, including a key penalty stop, but the Toreros couldn't overcome the two goals conceded in the first half. The team is set to host LMU on Saturday for Pop Culture Night.
- San Diego's record stands at 4-4-6, with a WCC record of 4-1-2.
- Ilise Medrano made six saves, including a penalty save, in her fifth start of the season.
- San Diego's defense struggled initially, conceding two goals in the first 62 minutes.
- Ella Callanan was the only player from San Diego to record shots on target during the match.
The Toreros will look to bounce back as they host LMU on Saturday, aiming to improve their league standing and performance at home.
Bottom LineDespite the loss, San Diego showcased resilience late in the game. The team's next match presents an opportunity to regain momentum as they continue their WCC campaign.
